x4freetext: Main Reference
Data Obtained from the Author
-Excitation Functions of (N,P) And (N,A) Reactions on
Molybdenum Isotopes.
H. Liskien and R. Widera. Experimental Site
For the Irradiation.
R. Woelfle and S.M. Qaim. Experimental Site
For the Activity Measurements.
The CN-Type Van De Graaff Accelerator of
CBNM Delivered a 38 Micro-Amp Deuteron Beam of 3183
keV Energy onto the Neutron Producing Target For
2.610 Days.
A 3 Mg/Cm2 T-Ti Target was Used. The Target
Was Backed by a 4 Cm Diameter Silver Sheet of 0.3 mm
Thickness, Fixed in an Aluminium Tube of 1 mm Wall
Thickness. The Silver Sheet was Cooled by a Thin
Water Film.
The Samples were Activated in Different
Angular Positions with Respect to the Beam Direction.
In this Way the Neutron Energy Variation with Angle
From the Source Reaction Could be Used For the Exci-
Tation Function Measurement.
The Neutron Source Intensity was Monitored
With a Directional Long Counter.
A Proton Recoil Telescope was Used For
Absolute Determination of the Neutron Fluence.
A Calibrated 35 Cm3 Geli Detector was Used to
Determine the Activity of the Samples.
A Proton Recoil Telescope,
Positioned at an Angle of 16 Degrees Relative to the
Deuteron Beam Direction and at a Source to Radiator
Distance of 80 Cm, was Used For the Absolute Fluence
Determination. The Fluence at Other Angles was Deter-
Mined by Using the Known Angular Distribution of the
Source Reaction. The Fluence Rates Averaged Over the
Sample Volumes were in the Range 0.6 to 1.8E+6
Neutrons/Cm2/Sec.
.In Addition, the Activities from the 13-Al-27/N,a/-
Reaction in the Aluminium Foils were Detected with
Gamma-Ray Spectroscopy Using the Same Equipment As
For the Activity Measurements For the Molybdenum
Sheets.
.The Metallic Samples were 2 Cm Diameter by 0.5 Cm
Thick Discs Made of 99.8 Percent Pure Molybdenum in
Its Natural Isotopic Composition. 15 Samples, Each
Sandwiched Between Two 2 Cm Diameter by 0.1 Cm Thick
Aluminium Sheets, were Suspended from a Graduated
Ring Adjusted with Its Center Above the Neutron Source
The Samples were Arranged Symmetrically to the Beam
Direction with a Source to Middle-Plane-Sample Dis-
Tance of 8.29 Cm.
.The Neutron Fluence Measurements with the Recoil Te-
Lescope were Corrected For Distortions by the Target
Assembly. The Activation of the Samples were Correc-
Ted For the Neutron Source Intensity Variations with
Time, Neutron Attenuation and Multiple Scattering.
The Count Rate in the Activity Measurements were Cor-
Rected For the Small Differences Between Counting and
Calibration Geometry, For Coincidence and Pile-Up
Losses and For Gamma Self-Absorption Within the
Samples.
.Correction For Deviation from Calibration
Geometry - 0.8%
Correction For Gamma-Ray Absorption  Within
The Sample - 2.4 -11.7%
Correction For Coincident Events - 4.5%
Correction For  Activity Uncertainty - 4.0 - 5.1%
Total Uncertainty. The Main Uncertainty
Contributions in the Neutron Fluence Measurements and
In the Activity Measurements are Given Below.
